The paper focuses on the interplay of computer vision and dialogue systems, specifically in the context of a guessing game that requires higher-level image understanding and language grounding. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces deep learning models to establish initial baselines, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the design decisions in collecting the dataset and the associated tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
